    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <head>359. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName>) to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName>, Washington, December
                    3, 1976.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d359fn1">Source: <persName
                            corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName> Library, National Security
                        Adviser, <gloss target="#t_nsc">NSC</gloss> Staff for East Asia and Pacific
                        Affairs Convenience File, Box 31, Breakthrough in Philippine Base
                        Negotiations. Secret; Sensitive. Sent for information. <persName
                            corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName> initialed the memorandum. The
                        draft of the joint U.S.-Philippine statement is ibid., Presidential Country
                        Files for East Asia and the Pacific, Box 15, Philippines (5)</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d359fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName> presented
                            <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName> with information on
                        the Philippine base negotiations.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1976-12-03">December 3, 1976</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>MEMORANDUM<lb/>THE WHITE HOUSE<lb/>WASHINGTON</p>
                <p>INFORMATION</p>
                <p>December 3, 1976</p>
                <p>MEMORANDUM FOR: THE PRESIDENT<lb/>FROM: BRENT <persName
                        corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">SCOWCROFT</persName> [BS initialed]</p>
                <p>SUBJECT: Breakthrough in Philippine Base Negotiations</p>
                <p>Philippine Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos"
                        >Romulo</persName> told Secretary <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a"
                        >Kissinger</persName> in Mexico City that his Government is prepared to
                    accept the billion-dollar financial package we offered as compensation for the
                    bases, on the assumption that all other issues are resolved to our satisfaction.
                    The five-year financial package which you approved would be broken down as
                    follows:</p>
                <table cols="2" rows="10">
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Military Assistance</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Grant Aid</cell>
                        <cell role="num">$200 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <gloss target="#t_fms">FMS</gloss> Financing</cell>
                        <cell role="num">$300 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell role="num">$500 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Economic Assistance</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Development Assistance</cell>
                        <cell role="num">$250 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <gloss target="#t_pl-480">PL 480</gloss> Loans</cell>
                        <cell role="num">$125 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Consideration of Exim Bank Loans</cell>
                        <cell role="num">$125 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell role="num">$500 million</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Total $ 1 billion</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>It would appear that President <persName corresp="#p_marcos-ferdinand"
                        >Marcos</persName> has decided that our financial offer was good enough to
                    nail down before the change in administrations. [<hi rend="italic">text not
                        declassified</hi>] Hopefully, <persName corresp="#p_marcos-ferdinand"
                        >Marcos</persName> will also share our desire to wind up the negotiations
                    promptly. Some potentially difficult issues remain, however:</p>
                <pb facs="d359-2" n="2" xml:id="d359-2"/>
                <p>— We still have to ensure that Philippine negotiators agree to provisions which
                    will allow us adequate operational freedom at the bases.</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>— We must square away language concerning the nature of our treaty commitment —
                    though this should not be too difficult.</p>
                <p>Next Steps</p>
                <p>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName> is trying
                    to work out a joint announcement which he could make with <persName
                        corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Romulo</persName> here in Washington on Saturday,
                    December 4. (A copy of the proposed text is attached at Tab A.) State plans to
                    brief key Senators and Congressmen (Sparkman, Humphrey, Case, Zablocki,
                    Broomfield, and Fascell), and Defense is considering the possibility of
                    informing the Armed Services leadership in the House and Senate.</p>
                <p>State and Defense are working urgently on negotiating instructions to Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_sullivan-william-h">Sullivan</persName> so that he
                    will be ready to begin talks next week and wind them up as rapidly as
                    possible.</p>
            </div>
